    "storefront": "us",
    "author_name": "chronolucca",
    "author_uri": "https://itunes.apple.com/us/reviews/id911979897",
    "title": "Ads",
    "text": "Ads are becoming more and more annoying and ruining the viewing experience more and more. I\u2019m catching on to all the cheap psychological tricks they do and o will not be giving them money to fix a problem that they caused in the first place. \n\nThey seem to also have lost complete with what makes sense as far as ad placement goes for certain types of videos. For example, long sleep & meditation videos should not have mid-roll ads but they do now. The way ads are served used to be in the creators control and YouTube has taken that away because they value increased profits over the user experience.\n\nAlso, km not against ads. I would say that Instagram in contrast is brilliant when it comes to serving me ads. I\u2019ve never been upset over an Instagram ad and that platform seems to know how to serve me ads that I actually want, save, use, and find helpful, but any time I see a YouTube ad, they are just making me absolutely despise whatever product or service is being served to me and guaranteeing that I will never use it \n\nI am so close to deleting the app, and employing alternative tactics to getting an ad free YouTube experience on my phone instead of using the app.",
    "rating": 1,
